Reiterating this point on Wednesday, the central bank said it is focused on “wholesale” CBDC uses cases. In April, the central bank said it is not looking to replace coins and banknotes.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
The European Central Bank&nbsp;<a href="https://www.theblockcrypto.com/post/49307/european-central-bank-is-in-favor-of-its-own-digital-currency-for-faster-and-cheaper-payments" data-v-f87c67ca="">also once said</a>&nbsp;that it is willing to issue its own digital currency if the private sector fails to make cross-border payments faster and cheaper.&nbsp;&nbsp;
